name: Cafe Ashwini

reviews.review_text:
I love goan brealfast espescially varities of bhaji and pav, so this time i was in panjim and found this place for breakfast, i ordered sangam bhaji (combination of rajma, beans, kaju etc) with goan bread called undo, taste of bhaji was totally well balanced and superb also their goan samosa was very good in taste.
This place is with small seating area so it was bit crowded at morning time.
Sorry Cafe Tato, cafe Ashwini is my new place for bhaji. Brilliant bhaji.

Most preffered breakfast place in Panjim.
Their mix bhaji is just awsome. This place happens to be very busy during breakfast time. Still lots of things to try

description:
### A Taste of Goa at Café Ashwini: A Review

Nestled in the charming area of Altinho in Panaji, Goa, Café Ashwini shines with an impressive rating of 4.3 from over 1,300 enthusiastic patrons. Renowned for its delectable Goan breakfast offerings, the café is a haven for lovers of local snacks. Guests often rave about their indulgent bhaji, freshly baked buns, and the quintessential pav, making it a standout establishment in the city. 

### Ambiance & Design

Café Ashwini boasts a cozy and inviting atmosphere, albeit with a small seating area that can get bustling during peak hours, particularly breakfast time. The warm, rustic decor is accented by simple wooden furniture and cheerful lighting, creating a welcome respite for those seeking comfort food. Customers have noted the slightly crowded vibe, particularly in the mornings, but this lively buzz only adds to the charm, reflecting the café's popularity among locals and tourists alike. 

### Menu & Culinary Experience

The star of the menu at Café Ashwini is undoubtedly its mix bhaji, which has received accolades for its perfect balance of flavors. One customer praised the Sangam bhaji—a delightful mélange of rajma, beans, and cashews paired with a Goan bread called 'undo'—as being particularly outstanding. The café also serves a variety of other Goan breakfast staples, including a well-received version of the traditional samosa, with many guests eager to explore further options on the extensive menu. With an array of savory snacks and competitive prices, there's something delightful for everyone.

### Customer Experience & Service

Guests have highlighted not only the quality of the food but also the friendliness of the staff, who contribute to the welcoming atmosphere. Service is efficient, ensuring diners enjoy their meals promptly, even during the busy morning rush. While reservations may not be common given the café's small size, the team seems adept at managing walk-ins, creating a pleasant experience for anyone stopping by.

### Popularity & Reviews

Café Ashwini has garnered a loyal following among breakfast enthusiasts, with numerous customers declaring it their new favorite spot for bhaji, comparing it favorably to other well-known local cafés. The buzz surrounding this café is palpable, with social media filled with mouthwatering photos of their breakfast creations, echoing the sentiments of satisfied diners eager to share their experiences.

### Utilizing Visual Content

The vibrant images shared by patrons capture the café's inviting ambiance and delicious dishes. One photo showcases a beautifully presented plate of bhaji, reflecting the colorful and appetizing nature of the Goan breakfast scene. Another highlights the lively setting, emphasizing the energetic atmosphere that patrons can expect during their visit. These visuals not only tantalize the senses but also encapsulate the warmth of Café Ashwini’s dining experience.

In conclusion, Café Ashwini is a must-visit for anyone craving authentic Goan breakfast fare in Panaji. With its consistency in quality, friendly service, and a menu that celebrates local flavors, it promises a delightful dining experience that leaves you wanting more. Give it a try, and immerse yourself in the culinary delights that Goa has to offer!
